<topic id="document-type-author-tab">
  <title>The Author Tab</title>
  <body>
    <p>The <uicontrol>Author</uicontrol> tab is a container that holds information regarding the CSS
      file used to render a document in the <uicontrol>Author</uicontrol> mode, and regarding
      framework-specific actions, menus, contextual menu, toolbar and content completion list of
      proposals. </p>
    <p>The options that you configure in the <uicontrol>Author</uicontrol> tab are grouped in the
      following sub-tabs:<ul>
        <li><xref href="the-css-sub-tab.dita#the-css-sub-tab"
          ><uicontrol>CSS</uicontrol></xref>;</li>
        <li><xref href="the-actions-sub-tab.dita#the-actions-sub-tab"
            ><uicontrol>Actions</uicontrol></xref>;</li>
        <li><xref href="the-menu-sub-tab.dita#the-menu-sub-tab"
          ><uicontrol>Menu</uicontrol></xref>;</li>
        <li><xref href="the-contextual-menu-sub-tab.dita#the-contextual-menu-sub-tab"
              ><uicontrol>Contextual menu</uicontrol></xref>;</li>
        <li><xref href="the-toolbar-tab.dita#the-toolbar-tab"
          ><uicontrol>Toolbar</uicontrol></xref>;</li>
        <li><xref href="the-content-completion-tab.dita#the-content-completion-tab"
              ><uicontrol>Content Completion</uicontrol></xref>.</li>
      </ul></p>
  </body>
